Given two strings s1 and s2 consisting of only lowercase characters whose anagrams are almost equal.
The task is to count the number of characters which needs to be deleted to make s1 equal to s2.

Example 1:

Input: s1 = "madame", s2 = "madam"
Output: 1
Explanation: string s1 = madame, string s2 = madam. Character 'e' in first string is need to be deleted to make S1 equal to S2.
Input: s1 = "suryansh", s2 = "suryanshzzawesome"
Output: 9
Explanation: string S1 = suryansh, string S2 = suryanshzzawesome. All character after "suryansh" in second string are need to be deleted to make S1 equal to S2.
Constraints:
1 <= s1, s2 <= 104

/*Function to count number of characters
 * to make s1 and s2 equal
 * s1 : first string
 * s2 : second string
 */
import java.util.Arrays;
class Geeks {

    static int coutChars(String s1, String s2) {

        // Your code here
        int []a = new int[26];
        int []b = new int[26];
        for(char c: s1.toCharArray()){
            a[c-'a']++;
        }
        for(char c: s2.toCharArray()){
            b[c-'a']++;
        }
        int del = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<26; i++){
            del += Math.abs(a[i] - b[i]);
        }
        return del;
        
    }
}
